race.comment: WATTEN ASSETT (6) had a little reset following his fresh run and that seemed to work last start at Echuca when he turned in a much better effort. Was only 0.3L away there and now rises in distance slightly. Third-up, drawn well and this looks a very suitable race. BASILICA (7) stuck on well in a good maiden at Seymour 21 days ago, ending up in third. She'll be better suited rising to this trip and she looks to have plenty of improvement to come. She can make an impression. BIG STAR (9) is building towards a maiden win, just missing as favourite at Yarra Valley 30 days ago. Needs some luck from out wide but rates highly on what she's done this time in work. MIDNIGHT EAGLE (4) comes here without a public outing but his debut effort was sound. Keep safe.
